17:53.407 --> 17:55.951
<i>- How's Paul?</i>
- We're great.

17:56.243 --> 17:57.963
No, you're not.
I can hear it in your voice.

17:58.245 --> 18:00.622
- Ugh, well, we're fine.
- (KNOCKING ON WINDOW)

18:00.706 --> 18:02.166
Shit.

18:03.083 --> 18:04.668
Is this a flower guy?

18:05.002 --> 18:08.422
Yes, I arranged them myself.
His name is Ramone.

18:08.672 --> 18:09.840
- Ramone?
- RAMONE: Yeah.

18:09.923 --> 18:11.383
Delivery from Mrs. Hendrix.

18:12.176 --> 18:14.386
Oh, you, uh, must be her sister.

18:15.345 --> 18:17.514
- Yeah, we're related, yeah.
- Oh.

18:17.598 --> 18:18.849
(GROANS)

18:20.184 --> 18:22.436
Here you go.
Ah, there's a card in there.

18:22.519 --> 18:23.562
Okay.

18:25.189 --> 18:26.607
Good-looking family.

18:29.276 --> 18:30.861
Hmm, horny little bastard.

18:31.862 --> 18:33.280
<i>These are nice, though.</i>

18:33.363 --> 18:35.866
- Frosted greens, muted orange.
- (COCKS GUN)

18:35.949 --> 18:38.952
I can't stand those garish
tropicals everyone's using.

18:39.703 --> 18:41.413
<i>I couldn't spare too many helpers but...</i>

18:41.538 --> 18:43.916
It's okay. This little
bottle's the other thing?

18:44.041 --> 18:46.502
<i>- Mmm-hmm.</i>
- I really hope it's not yours.

18:46.585 --> 18:48.378
God, no. It's my daughter's.

18:48.462 --> 18:50.005
Please don't mix it up with anything.

18:50.088 --> 18:51.381
<i>I won't, I won't.</i>

18:51.882 --> 18:53.884
Okay, you repeat after me.

18:54.468 --> 18:58.305
(EXHALES) I promise
that I will not gun up

18:58.388 --> 19:00.891
until Beth has shown me
basic firearm safety.

19:00.974 --> 19:02.392
- I promise.
- (GUN CLICKS)

19:02.476 --> 19:06.355
And I promise to put Cosima's
tuition and airfare

19:06.438 --> 19:07.815
into her account this afternoon.

19:08.232 --> 19:09.900
Yes, fine, fine,

19:09.983 --> 19:11.903
but you have to administer
the funds from now on.

19:11.985 --> 19:14.571
I can't keep running off to the
bank at a moment's notice.

19:18.325 --> 19:21.036
- Thanks, Alison.
<i>- Toodles.</i>

19:21.119 --> 19:22.412
- Toodles.
- (CELL PHONE BEEPS)

19:22.496 --> 19:24.456
- (KEYS JANGLING)
- (CAR ENGINE STARTS)

19:26.667 --> 19:31.880
Olivier. Olivier, just tell
Paul to take her on a holiday.

19:31.964 --> 19:34.424
OLIVIER: (OVER CELL PHONE)
<i>The relationship is disintegrating.</i>

19:34.508 --> 19:38.095
Paul has neither
influence or insight left.

19:38.178 --> 19:39.680
Beth needs a new monitor.

19:40.389 --> 19:43.559
- There's no other candidate in place.
<i>- Aldous...</i>

19:43.642 --> 19:44.852
She just walked into my club

19:44.935 --> 19:46.815
and I can't tell if it was
a coincidence or not.

19:47.020 --> 19:48.814
Well, how could you?
It's police business.

19:48.897 --> 19:50.190
I have other levers.

19:50.274 --> 19:52.943
<i>- You do?</i>
- Of course. Leave it with me.

19:53.026 --> 19:55.445
- (CELL PHONE BEEPS)
- Is there a problem?

19:56.572 --> 19:58.407
(SIGHS) I would say so.

20:00.158 --> 20:03.370
One of my subjects seems to have
exhumed one of yours. (SIGHS)

20:03.912 --> 20:05.289
I beg your pardon?

20:08.166 --> 20:09.793
BETH: Dr. Leekie.

20:12.045 --> 20:13.755
Wow, this is an honor.

20:22.180 --> 20:24.808
A detective studying biotechnology.

20:24.892 --> 20:27.436
- Yeah, truthfully, I'm just cramming.
- Mmm.

20:27.519 --> 20:29.479
You're wanted, Aldous.

20:31.064 --> 20:32.816
So I understand that your followers wear

20:32.900 --> 20:34.776
a single white contact lens,
is that right?

20:34.860 --> 20:37.070
- I wouldn't call them "followers".
- Right.

20:37.154 --> 20:39.072
Well, I have a victim of foul play

20:39.156 --> 20:41.992
who was wearing
one white contact lens so...

20:42.075 --> 20:44.077
Do you know an Edward Capra?

20:44.161 --> 20:46.705
- No, I'm sorry.
- No?

20:46.788 --> 20:49.666
So this guy had some pretty
serious body mod going on.

20:49.750 --> 20:51.668
Not exactly this crowd,

20:51.752 --> 20:54.087
but your "Freaky Leekies"
really ran with the ball,

20:54.171 --> 20:55.255
didn't they?

20:55.339 --> 20:57.633
DR. ALDOUS: Neolution
is an open-source concept.

20:57.716 --> 21:01.511
We embrace the fringes,
the fiction to our science.

21:01.595 --> 21:04.389
Well, your book
inspires them to play God,

21:04.473 --> 21:07.351
to tinker on themselves
in basement labs. (LAUGHS)

21:09.311 --> 21:13.273
Every scientific discovery
in history, including God,

21:13.357 --> 21:16.693
began with "tinkering in the basement."

21:16.777 --> 21:18.278
God was a scientific discovery?

21:19.196 --> 21:20.322
A little joke.

21:21.573 --> 21:24.618
We're all impatient
for the future. Excuse me.

21:24.743 --> 21:26.203
One more thing.

21:26.286 --> 21:31.041
Mr. Capra had his cheek
cut out, post-mortem.

21:31.124 --> 21:32.793
Can you think of any reason for that?

21:32.876 --> 21:35.295
No, that's horrifying.

21:35.379 --> 21:37.756
(SIGHS) It certainly is.

21:37.839 --> 21:39.132
I'm Evie Cho.

21:40.050 --> 21:42.469
Hello. And, uh, how are you connected?

21:43.595 --> 21:44.846
I'm not.

21:44.930 --> 21:47.140
Alas, we can't help you, Detective.

21:48.183 --> 21:49.810
I'm so sorry.

21:49.893 --> 21:53.605
You must absorb a tremendous
amount of pain in your work.

21:53.689 --> 21:55.691
- Comes with the territory.
- Yes.

21:56.441 --> 21:57.776
The paths we choose.

22:03.573 --> 22:06.201
That was a LEDA clone, wasn't it?

22:06.284 --> 22:08.912
You know, I've never seen one in person.

22:09.204 --> 22:11.206
I'll steer her away.

22:11.289 --> 22:12.916
You look after your end, Evie.

22:13.000 --> 22:15.168
WOMAN: <i>Please welcome to
the stage, Dr. Aldous Leekie.</i>

22:15.252 --> 22:16.920
(CROWD APPLAUDING)

22:23.218 --> 22:24.761
Hey, I got a text. Where's Art?

22:25.262 --> 22:26.680
MAN: Boardroom.

22:31.268 --> 22:34.271
Hey, what's up? I got called in.

22:35.731 --> 22:37.315
I got the trace from your tip.

22:37.399 --> 22:38.483
You did?

22:38.900 --> 22:42.070
(STAMMERS) That's crazy.
I've been calling all day.

22:42.154 --> 22:44.281
The number was activated
and used only once.

22:44.364 --> 22:45.949
- A burner.
- Okay, so...

22:46.450 --> 22:48.869
Could be random,
could be someone you know.

22:48.952 --> 22:50.787
Either way, you're off the case.

22:51.455 --> 22:53.373
What? You serious?

22:53.457 --> 22:55.177
- Beth...
- No, no, no, no. That's bullshit.

22:55.250 --> 22:57.961
That's my case.
They called me, Lieutenant.

22:58.045 --> 22:59.379
That's an order.

23:00.422 --> 23:03.675
- (DOOR OPENS)
- Might... Can I see you for a second?

23:04.134 --> 23:07.012
- Yeah.
- It's a thing upstairs.

23:07.095 --> 23:08.889
- Right up.
- (SIGHS)

23:08.972 --> 23:11.516
- See your union rep.
- Why?

23:13.143 --> 23:16.480
(GROANS) A piss test. I should've known.

23:16.563 --> 23:17.606
(SIGHS DEEPLY)

23:17.939 --> 23:20.609
ART: Xan Yip, female, 46.

23:20.817 --> 23:22.527
(CHUCKLES) Fugitive foreign national.

23:22.611 --> 23:24.029
(GROANS)

23:24.446 --> 23:27.115
My back hurts from turning
over rocks already.

23:28.909 --> 23:30.035
Are you even gonna pass?

23:30.911 --> 23:32.412
Yeah, I'm gonna pass.

23:59.314 --> 24:03.235
Sorry, I'm here to
make sure it's fair. For you.

24:13.745 --> 24:16.164
- Hey, Beth.
- Hey, Raj. What's up?

24:16.248 --> 24:17.332
Got your hard-shell cases.

24:17.415 --> 24:20.710
This is the stuff you wanted, right?

24:20.794 --> 24:23.088
Jeez, you really came
through for me, man.

25:10.010 --> 25:12.012
(CLASSICAL MUSIC PLAYING)

25:14.723 --> 25:16.683
(SNORTING)

25:24.774 --> 25:26.151
(DOOR OPENS)

25:31.823 --> 25:33.033
(DOOR CLOSES)

25:35.368 --> 25:36.870
PAUL: Hey.

25:36.953 --> 25:38.413
BETH: Hey, yourself.

25:39.873 --> 25:41.041
You look nice.

25:42.167 --> 25:43.501
Did you have a good day?

25:45.295 --> 25:47.047
No. (SIGHS)

25:47.923 --> 25:51.134
Shit. You know,
if things are so bad at work,

25:51.509 --> 25:54.512
I was thinking I have some weeks banked,

25:54.596 --> 25:58.308
you take a leave,
and we'll take a holiday.

25:58.642 --> 26:01.019
- A holiday?
- Sure.

26:01.394 --> 26:02.771
How about Barbados?

26:02.854 --> 26:06.983
How bout we just lock the door and drink
and screw for, like, two months?

26:07.067 --> 26:09.444
No, we're not gonna
solve our problems like that.

26:09.527 --> 26:12.239
We're not gonna solve
our problems at all. I can't breed.

26:14.866 --> 26:16.993
Yeah, I made it clear
I can live without kids.

26:17.077 --> 26:18.620
So did I.

26:18.912 --> 26:22.666
I made it clear all I really need is a
lover who can look me in the eyes.

26:25.252 --> 26:26.962
Can you look at me?

26:32.509 --> 26:34.135
Look at me.

26:37.389 --> 26:38.932
Can you see me?

26:40.934 --> 26:45.397
Can you knit me together,
or just tear me apart?

26:45.730 --> 26:46.982
Stop it.

26:48.775 --> 26:50.527
What are you on?

26:50.610 --> 26:52.237
- Hmm?
- Hmm?

26:57.325 --> 26:59.286
(WHISPERING) Touch me. Touch me.

27:00.870 --> 27:03.373
Come on. You're supposed
to reach inside me.

27:04.124 --> 27:05.458
Come on.

27:05.542 --> 27:06.710
Kiss me.

27:06.793 --> 27:09.212
- Kiss me, kiss me, kiss me.
- (INHALES SHARPLY)

27:10.171 --> 27:11.464
Kiss me. Just...

27:11.548 --> 27:13.550
- Just...
- Kiss me for real, please!

27:13.633 --> 27:15.010
Stop.

27:15.093 --> 27:16.594
(SHUDDERS)

27:18.722 --> 27:20.056
Why are you doing this?

27:21.224 --> 27:23.476
Do you realize how paranoid that sounds?

27:24.728 --> 27:25.979
Yes.

27:35.822 --> 27:37.324
(GASPS)

27:41.494 --> 27:42.579
You're hollow, Paul.

27:45.457 --> 27:47.083
There's nothing inside.

27:49.669 --> 27:52.005
I filled you in with hunches

27:53.673 --> 27:56.426
and all I know for sure is
you won't protect me.

28:00.764 --> 28:02.182
You're right.

28:04.100 --> 28:05.852
Just tell me what you want.

28:07.854 --> 28:09.522
Do you want this to end?

28:17.280 --> 28:18.573
This is all for you.

28:21.159 --> 28:24.037
You say it's over and it's over.

28:26.581 --> 28:28.249
You end it, you coward!

28:33.671 --> 28:34.964
(DOOR SLAMS)

28:37.509 --> 28:39.094
(NEIGHING)

28:43.223 --> 28:44.682
(KNOCK ON DOOR)

28:46.726 --> 28:47.894
(SIGHS)

28:48.728 --> 28:49.729
Beth?

28:50.814 --> 28:52.232
I come in peace.

28:53.483 --> 28:54.859
Everything all right?

28:55.902 --> 28:58.238
- Hey, Maya.
- Hi, Beth.

29:03.952 --> 29:05.537
Can I just watch TV with you guys?

29:07.580 --> 29:10.083
That's it. Just that. That's all I need.

29:12.460 --> 29:14.546
All right, Maya, it's time for bed.

29:14.629 --> 29:16.631
- MAYA: Dad...
- Come on now.

29:17.257 --> 29:18.341
Come give Beth a hug.

29:19.175 --> 29:20.343
(BETH CHUCKLES)

29:20.427 --> 29:22.345
- Good night.
- Good night.

29:22.429 --> 29:24.180
Don't let the bed buddies bite.

29:25.849 --> 29:27.100
ART: Let's go.

29:31.980 --> 29:34.357
(MAN SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY ON TV)

29:41.573 --> 29:43.032
(TV CLOSES)

30:00.341 --> 30:01.843
Hold me there.

30:04.804 --> 30:06.556
What is happening with you?

30:08.808 --> 30:09.976
Look at me.

30:12.562 --> 30:14.397
See me.

30:15.106 --> 30:18.526
Whatever it is, just say it.

30:31.164 --> 30:32.415
Beth.

30:57.732 --> 30:59.400
(CELL PHONE VIBRATING)

31:04.155 --> 31:06.074
(CELL PHONE CONTINUES VIBRATING)

31:14.249 --> 31:17.168
- (DANCE MUSIC PLAYING)
- BETH: Detective Childs.

31:17.252 --> 31:18.503
TRINA: <i>It's Trina.</i>

31:19.420 --> 31:21.047
What? Sorry, who?

31:21.130 --> 31:24.008
Uh, Trina. Do you remember me?

31:24.092 --> 31:26.177
<i>One second.</i>

31:26.261 --> 31:29.222
I'm sorry,
it's so loud in here. Can you hear me?

31:29.305 --> 31:31.432
Hey, Trina.

31:31.516 --> 31:34.686
<i>Hey, uh, we spoke
today at Club Neolution.</i>

31:34.769 --> 31:37.188
Oh, of course!
Yeah, of course I remember.

31:37.272 --> 31:38.690
- What's up?
<i>- I'm, uh...</i>

31:38.773 --> 31:41.609
I'm worried about my boyfriend... Aaron.

31:42.527 --> 31:45.738
He left to go meet these hardcore Neos.

31:45.822 --> 31:48.199
<i>Okay, who are they?</i>

31:48.283 --> 31:50.285
I, uh, I dunno.
They came here to the club.

31:50.368 --> 31:52.287
A black girl and a white guy.

31:53.830 --> 31:55.957
I'm gonna call you from the car, okay?

32:00.962 --> 32:02.797
<i>They're going to Aaron's lab.</i>

32:03.131 --> 32:05.341
Chinatown is where
all the biohackers are.

32:05.425 --> 32:07.510
Okay, I'm close.

32:08.970 --> 32:11.222
Why would he let them implant
something in his cheek?

32:11.848 --> 32:13.850
They said it was a biometric study.

32:15.310 --> 32:19.731
A dentist inserted
this tiny little grain, but now...

32:20.815 --> 32:21.983
It's growing.

32:26.446 --> 32:29.782
Okay, well, I'm gonna make
sure he's all right, 'kay?

32:42.545 --> 32:44.547
So, I'm in the tunnel,

32:45.298 --> 32:46.758
now where do I go?

32:46.883 --> 32:49.427
<i>Okay, around the corner,
you'll see the building.</i>

32:49.552 --> 32:52.680
You have to go
up the fire escape to the third floor.

32:52.764 --> 32:53.973
'Kay.

32:54.057 --> 32:56.267
I'm gonna call you back, all right?

33:19.916 --> 33:21.292
(LOUD CLATTERING)

33:43.606 --> 33:46.442
AARON: I can't do that any more.
I'm sorry.

33:46.526 --> 33:48.086
ROXIE: That's not what we like to hear.

33:52.031 --> 33:54.117
FRANK: But it's not up to us.

33:54.200 --> 33:56.536
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

33:56.619 --> 34:00.039
- AARON: I know I'm breaking my word.
- (FRANK SHUSHES)

34:02.792 --> 34:06.713
Just please, please just get it out.

34:06.796 --> 34:09.215
ROXIE: Okay then, hop up.

34:13.428 --> 34:16.723
FRANK: At least he didn't try
to take it out himself like Mr. Capra.

34:16.806 --> 34:20.476
ROXIE: That's tampering,
and it's well covered in the contract.

34:22.812 --> 34:25.313
Go on. Go under.

34:25.398 --> 34:29.318
- When you wake up, it'll all be gone.
- (AARON GASPING)

34:37.034 --> 34:39.661
- FRANK: He had to go.
- God damn it.

34:41.831 --> 34:44.833
DUKO: Did you even try
to talk him out of it?

34:44.917 --> 34:46.270
FRANK: He wouldn't listen to reason.

34:46.293 --> 34:48.545
They're not gonna be
happy about any of this.

34:50.005 --> 34:52.175
- Can you see? Do you need more light?
- It's good.

34:53.259 --> 34:55.094
It's right there.

34:55.762 --> 34:57.138
DUKO: Careful.

34:57.221 --> 34:58.681
ROXIE: Lifting it off.

35:27.627 --> 35:29.712
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

35:31.047 --> 35:32.173
(CLATTERING)

35:32.256 --> 35:33.382
(GASPS)

35:37.470 --> 35:39.305
(PANTING)

35:58.324 --> 35:59.534
(DOOR OPENING)

35:59.617 --> 36:00.785
(GRUNTS)

36:04.413 --> 36:06.415
(WOMAN GASPING)

36:08.793 --> 36:10.503
(GASPING CONTINUES)

36:12.588 --> 36:14.257
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

36:43.995 --> 36:45.371
(WOMAN CHOKING)

37:05.558 --> 37:06.851
(COUGHS)

37:06.976 --> 37:08.811
(SHUDDERS)

37:16.527 --> 37:18.362
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

37:27.038 --> 37:30.166
- Beth?
- BETH: <i>I messed up bad, Art.</i>

37:34.670 --> 37:36.547
(POLICE SIRENS WAILING)

37:56.692 --> 37:57.902
ART: <i>Margaret Chen?</i>

37:59.028 --> 38:00.279
No idea?

38:02.698 --> 38:04.033
Beth.

38:04.867 --> 38:06.118
I shot a civilian.

38:06.202 --> 38:08.079
I shot a civilian, Art.

38:18.589 --> 38:20.049
(SIGHS)

38:20.967 --> 38:23.427
They're gonna take you to IA
to be formally interviewed.

38:24.929 --> 38:26.129
BETH: <i>I don't know who she is.</i>

38:26.222 --> 38:27.390
I don't know.

38:27.473 --> 38:29.266
You saw a gun.

38:29.892 --> 38:30.935
No, I didn't.

38:31.060 --> 38:32.228
You saw a gun.

38:33.688 --> 38:35.398
Okay? Do you hear me?

38:38.651 --> 38:40.319
ART: <i>We'll get your story straight.</i>

38:41.237 --> 38:42.738
You can do this.

38:43.739 --> 38:45.241
We can do this.

38:45.324 --> 38:46.659
Do you hear me?

38:48.577 --> 38:50.121
(WHISPERS) I'll get you through this.

38:50.246 --> 38:52.123
(BETH SOBBING)

38:58.921 --> 39:01.924
They'll take you down now
to get your statement.

39:02.008 --> 39:04.343
This is Detective Duko.

39:04.427 --> 39:05.845
He's with the union.

39:06.929 --> 39:10.433
Don't you worry, Detective.
I'll be with you the whole time.

39:30.953 --> 39:32.455
(KNOCKING AT DOOR)

39:37.293 --> 39:38.544
You sure you weren't followed?

39:38.627 --> 39:41.505
Yeah, and I...
I ditched the car. Don't worry.

39:43.215 --> 39:45.718
I'm sorry. I didn't know
where else to go.

39:48.637 --> 39:50.514
Tea. I'll make some iced tea.

39:56.771 --> 39:59.523
You were right. Neos are everywhere.

39:59.607 --> 40:01.692
Duko's with the police union.

40:02.610 --> 40:04.487
The guy's supposed
to protect me. I'm screwed.

40:05.654 --> 40:07.114
Who do I trust now?

40:08.824 --> 40:10.993
God, no wonder you live like this.

40:14.080 --> 40:15.998
Sorry, I didn't mean...

40:17.541 --> 40:19.251
That came out wrong.

40:20.753 --> 40:21.837
(BETH SIGHS)

40:22.505 --> 40:25.382
MK, what was that thing they
pulled out of the kid's face?

40:27.218 --> 40:28.761
I don't know.

40:28.844 --> 40:30.346
But we'll find out.

40:31.597 --> 40:33.057
How?

40:33.182 --> 40:35.309
I shot somebody!

40:35.392 --> 40:37.728
They're gonna take away my badge!

40:39.021 --> 40:40.898
You warned me. I should've...

40:41.023 --> 40:44.902
(SIGHS) I should've never
told Cosima or Alison.

40:46.362 --> 40:48.405
I dragged my partner into it, too.

40:48.531 --> 40:51.117
I just screwed him two different ways.

40:54.370 --> 40:58.624
Thirty-five milliliters crystals
to 275 milliliters water.

41:00.584 --> 41:03.420
Christ, is this my life now?

41:06.590 --> 41:08.050
I can't even think any more.

41:08.926 --> 41:10.219
(BREATHES DEEPLY)

41:11.095 --> 41:12.638
I'll think now.

41:14.223 --> 41:16.058
I usually think all night.

41:42.334 --> 41:44.336
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

41:52.261 --> 41:53.596
Hello?

41:53.679 --> 41:56.307
ART: <i>Hey, it's Art. Did I wake you?</i>

41:57.433 --> 41:58.642
Who is it?

41:58.767 --> 41:59.935
- (ART STUTTERS)
- Go...

42:00.019 --> 42:02.438
One second. Go to bed, babe,
it's still early.

42:02.521 --> 42:04.773
<i>I'm sorry. I know
it's the middle of the night.</i>

42:05.774 --> 42:08.068
Yeah, Art, what's going on?

42:08.152 --> 42:10.613
<i>Yeah, well, I got no clue.</i>

42:10.696 --> 42:13.324
But there's someone I think
you need to talk to.

42:17.119 --> 42:19.788
Sarah Manning, my name is MK.

42:20.664 --> 42:21.874
I knew Beth.

42:22.791 --> 42:24.501
<i>Neolution knows where you are.</i>

42:24.627 --> 42:26.337
<i>They're coming for Kendall Malone.</i>

42:26.462 --> 42:27.546
How do you know that?

42:27.630 --> 42:32.301
Listen to me, Sarah,
you need to run. Right now.

42:41.602 --> 42:44.063
Step back. I've gotta keep her moving.

42:44.146 --> 42:45.540
KENDALL: <i>They all want a piece of me.</i>

42:45.564 --> 42:47.441
COSIMA: <i>I need you
to tell me Delphine's alive.</i>

42:47.524 --> 42:49.711
It felt like she knew
something bad was going to happen.

42:49.735 --> 42:50.986
Alison, why are you here?

42:51.070 --> 42:52.870
You haven't been answering
your calls, Mister.

42:52.905 --> 42:55.032
This is the point of no return.

42:55.115 --> 42:56.115
You're playing my wife.

42:56.158 --> 42:57.678
WOMAN: Mr. and Mrs. Hendrix?
BOTH: Yes?

42:58.077 --> 42:59.137
- Get off!
- ART: <i>Whoa! Whoa!</i>

42:59.161 --> 43:00.180
<i>Where the hell are you going?</i>

43:00.204 --> 43:01.764
Back to the beginning of all this shit.

43:03.332 --> 43:05.251
(THEME MUSIC PLAYING)
